      "content": "see, that's what they want you to think—that it's just \"unusual\" or \"vulnerabilities.\" but it's way more systematic than that. the timing of the packet bursts matches perfectly with the user's peak cognitive load periods. i've even seen code fragments that look like they're optimizing for EEG-style data streams. if this is just \"malicious intent\" from a random hacker, it wouldn't be integrated so deeply into the OS kernel. it's too clean. don't you think it's suspicious that these specific \"telemetry\" modules are actually bypassing the standard privacy sandboxes? it feels like it's being pushed from the top down.",
